{
  "texts": [
    "In data-driven supervised approaches, the larger the available training set the more resilience to data noise is achieved.",
    "However, real-world scenarios are often characterized by limited (or none) labeled data availability.",
    "In the literature, common knowledge is known for improving the robustness to noise of HAR models in labeled data scarcity settings [6].",
    "Considering ADL-LLM, the common knowledge encoded in the LLM should help to identify activities even when some of the sensors are noisy or fail to provide data.",
    "Nonetheless, when data is too noisy or the amount of missing information is significant, both ADL-LLM and classic data-driven solutions would lead to poor results."
  ]
}